[{"id":"VR876930","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Which of the following correctly indicates the direction of the net magnetic force on the loop and provides a valid justification?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR876930_rubric","features":[{"type":"sharedpassage","html":"<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A rectangular conducting loop is moving to the right at a constant speed as it enters a region of uniform magnetic field that is directed out of the plane of the figure, as shown. The top, right, bottom, and left segments of the loop are labeled <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Q\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"Q\" overflow=\"scroll\"> <mtext>Q</mtext> </math></span></span>, <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"R\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"R\" overflow=\"scroll\"> <mtext>R</mtext> </math></span></span>, <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"S\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"S\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>S</mtext></math></span></span>, and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"T\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"T\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>T</mtext></math></span></span>, respectively.</p>\n&nbsp;\n\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a rectangular loop moving to the right into a uniform magnetic field that is directed out of the page. The top, right, bottom, and left segments of the loop are labeled Q, R, S, and T, respectively. Right segment R is entirely inside the magnetic field while left segment T is entirely outside the magnetic field. Top and bottom segments Q and S are each approximately half inside and half outside the magnetic field.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR876930.g01.svg\" /></div>\n"}],"choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">To the left, because a leftward force is exerted on Segment <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"R\"><math alttext=\"R\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>R</mtext></math></span></span>, no force is exerted on Segment <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"T\"><math alttext=\"T\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>T</mtext></math></span></span>, and the forces exerted on Segment <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Q\"><math alttext=\"Q\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>Q</mtext></math></span></span> and Segment <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"S\"><math alttext=\"S\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>S</mtext></math></span></span> are equal and opposite</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">To the left, because a leftward force is exerted on both Segment <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Q\"><math alttext=\"Q\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>Q</mtext></math></span></span> and Segment <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"S\"><math alttext=\"S\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>S</mtext></math></span></span>, and no forces are exerted on Segment <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"R\"><math alttext=\"R\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>R</mtext></math></span></span> and Segment <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"T\"><math alttext=\"T\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>T</mtext></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">No direction, because the velocity of the loop is constant and therefore no magnetic forces are exerted on any of the loop segments</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">No direction, because the forces exerted on opposite segments are equal and opposite and therefore the net force on the loop is zero</p>"],"answer":0}]